Column Aliases
We can mention them after the column name. If there is a space in the string denoting the alias, then the use of double quotes around the string denoting 
the alias is mandatory. We can also use the keyword AS between the name of the column and the alias. The following query covers all the possible options 
for the alias:
SELECT title AS "Film Title", release_year "Year of Release",description AS Summary, original_language_id Language FROM film;
