NULL is a special marker in the database which represents the absence of any value. It does not mean zero (in case of numeric columns) or an empty string 
(for character or string columns). It just means there is no value at all. It was introduced by who proposed the relation data model first. It is
a keyword in any relational database. NULL is a state, not a value. The output of the following query shows us the NULL in the last column mentioned in 
the
SELECT title, description, original_language_id FROM film;
